The paper deals with the extension complexity of polytopes, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of closure properties of languages, which is a topic in computer science theory (cs.TH) and formal languages (cs.FL). Finally, the application of the results to problems in streaming models suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
